	<block>
		<h4 flex row middle>
			Strict mode
		</h4>
		<p>SurrealDB now supports the ability to startup in strict mode. When running in strict mode, all <code>NAMESPACE</code>, <code>DATABASE</code>, and <code>TABLE</code> definitions will not be created automatically when data is inserted. Instead if the selected namespace, database, or table has not been specifically defined, then the query will return an error.</p>
	</block>
	<block>
		<Code @name="docs-releases-1-0-0-beta-4-strict.shell">
			user@localhost % surreal start --strict --log debug --user root --pass root memory
		</Code>
	</block>
</Layout::Blocks>